caption: The service is excellent as always Best Italian in SoCal ! Great variety in the menu and excellent execution.  High quality ingredients. Very friendly staff and great service. Fairly causal and bustling ambience. Seating is fairly tight, but fine. Must try!
Best place to eat ever!

It's small, but welcoming and comfortable. We ate at the bar so I could watch the bar tender doing his thing. The fool was simply stunning. The big dare was a tortilla with salt cod, and it ended up being our #1, though it had to fight with the anchovies on toast with some magical thing they claim is butter for that honor. My friend lives in the neighborhood, and she calls it her "neighborhood spot". I would be there every night!

The service is particularly good and you will leave with a smile on your face. This restaurant is the most renowned and most visited place in my area.  The food here is quite simply unbelievable, the textures, flavors, and tastes unlike anywhere else I have ever been to. Highly recommended!

One of my favorite restaurants. I am continually impressed, especially at their ability to make vegetarian dishes shine (I usually prefer meat-centered dishes, but without fail, some of favorite items are the veggie small plates)! They pack so much flavor in the most unassuming of dishes. Highly recommend, take-out was even amazing!

Had takeout from here and it was delicious! Relatively simple food, but with that extra notch that you can’t get while cooking at home, and feels very clean and healthy too. Had the faro salad, butternut squash/carrots, pork bolognese and basque cake. All very good and reasonably priced. Probably my favorite restaurant in the area, and that’s saying something given there’s a lot of good restaurants around!

First time writing a review! I can’t believe how many times I said “oh my god” after taking a bite. I ordered the pork Bolognese and the chorizo, zest of the tomatoes, creaminess of the cheese and the perfectly al dente penne...perfection. Too bad they only have pickup/delivery right now because of the pandemic. I went inside to pick up my order and the place itself could not have more of a quaint, romantic feel. Delicious and possibly my new favorite restaurant in lake view, thank you!

This is a great restaurant! The food is delicious, the service is superb, and the atmosphere is great. It is a small place and more difficult for larger groups, but they were able to accommodate us. It is a tapas restaurant, so make sure you order a few different things and share with a group!
Fantastic !!
A top site for delicious seafood. bring your hunger - portions are large.
Outstanding location for tasty seafood. The service was helpful and kind. This place has a good atmosphere.
The fresh coconuts are the best! Natural flavor drink and the meat is tender while still cool.
meal was perfect, food was a masterpiece, overall amazing

Have been here twice, and was really satisfied both times. The food is really tasty and the price point is nice. It’s a small place with a lot of charm. And the drinks were good as well. The service is very friendly and prompt.
Love this place.
The food was ok. A bit over priced. We felt rushed and left early so the people waiting on the stoop could be seated.
Very intimate restaurant with great food and drinks! Didn't disappoint!!!
The seafood with pasta and the beef cheek and tasty, tiny space but great ambience

Stop in for a quick lunch.  Smooth layed back atmosphere.  My server Berlin was not only extremely polite, but made great recommendation; making my experience not only appetising but enjoyable as well. I will definitely return, and recommend to friends and family.
Food is delicious. Needs more bread and water. If I'm gonna pay this much for small plates, I'd better not run out of water. Which I did a few times, just ... How come? Leave me with a pitcher plz?
Like you needed my review to tell you this place is amazing
Amazingly friendly and knowledgeable staff, love the menu and the food. Will come back as often as I can!

We ate at the chef's corner at the bar on a Saturday night... great service all around, and everyone in the kitchen was friendly as we stared and watched their preparations.  My husband and I each had 2 cocktails.  They were well balanced and creative.  We started with the ceviche, which was small but delicious and a great way to open up our palettes.    We then had the prawn heads---- we had never had anything like it before, so it was a novelty, but they were good and the sauce was delicious.  I needed the bread service for the sauce!  We had the beets with goat cheese next, which was underwhelming and standard... it wasn't bad, just didn't knock us out.  This was followed by their specialty, which was the scallops.  They were big, buttery, and out of control delicious, and priced well.  A highlight for sure.  We finished with the braised beef.  It was super oniony but tender and delicious.  Definitely heavy.  We also had the basque cake which was great, but could have used some cream or ice cream.  The bill was $160 ($180 with tax) so it was not cheap, but it was so good and service was on point, so we did not mind at all.  I'm giving 4 stars and not 5 because the restaurant was SO HOT.  When I went to the bathroom, it was 20 degrees hotter in there.  We were sitting right by the kitchen, but our server told us there is poor ventilation and it's also uncomfortable in the summer.  I would definitely recommend the restaurant, but advise people to layer in a way that makes taking off layers doable!  We will return.
Amazing food. Amazing service. Amazing staff.

Reservations are a must because this space is small. I thoroughly enjoyed dining at mfk. last night. The service is prompt and provided a comfortable pace without feeling rushed or forgotten. Everything from the butter to the sardines to the scallops to the amazing tortilla espanola to the basque cake was delicious. The cocktails were tasty and unusual and Ben's wine recommendation was the perfect pairing. Can't wait to go back!

This place is phenomenal! I love a smaller restaurant and ordering lots of plates to try everything. I couldn’t be happier. The server was great and answered all of our questions, even steering us to other dishes when it wasn’t what we wanted. I will be back! Great, local spot!
I'll be back here for sure!

So this place was a 100% match for that google said  so I was supper excited about  dining there. Well needless to say all the food was delicious besides one dish that me and my date ordered  we order the tuna salad it tasted like tuna that came out of a 90cent can from the local grocery store it was disgusting not worth 12$, and if your a bigger person like I am 6"1 195lbs good luck fitting in the tables to sit it's very small.    I dont think I'll be back
One of my go-to places to grab some food. excellent location, always clean, and excellent service. I highly recommend them!
Great dinner. Excellent seafood, wine, service.

Reservations are a must because this space is small. I thoroughly enjoyed dining at mfk. last night. The service is prompt and provided a comfortable pace without feeling rushed or forgotten. Everything from the butter to the sardines to the scallops to the amazing tortilla espanola to the basque cake was delicious. The cocktails were tasty and unusual and Ben's wine recommendation was the perfect pairing. Can't wait to go back!

Small restaurant with good seafood options. Recommend reservations and parking may be an issue. Spanish Basque oriented food. Caipirinhas and white wine with dinner. The Tapas de Jamon was a great spreadable and shareable starter. The pea salad was excellent. I tried the prawn heads and was wary because of a past Chinatown experience but these were fine. Share the Seafood Fideos also excellent. We came early but restaurant filled up quickly and noise level was fine. Only why didn't rate 5 star as the restaurant does not do any special orders or changes to dishes. Looking forward to returning and trying more offerings from this great little restaurant.
The croquettes are excellent!!

Tried the croquette, smoked trout toast and braised beet salad. They tasted really good. A little bit pricey but it’s similar to any other tapas. Took one point off because of the long wait time between dishes.

A bit pricey with so-so service. $10 for three, small 1/8 inch slices of a baguette with a bit of tomato rubbed on it seems like a money grab and not in the generous spirit of pan con tomate found in the typical Catalonian restaurant that made the dish famous. Similarly $12 for 4 anchovies seems similarly ungenerous in spirit.  $36 ofr a small hangar steak--ditto. The wine selection is tiny. The service is overwhelmed when busy.  So I will not be back until they regain the right motives that made it a favorite in the past.

Great tapas! Staff has solid recommendations and the kitchen is turning out delicious, interesting food! Not on the menu, but there is a good little selection of Vermouths if you ask. Casey (?) is fantastic! Thank you for a great meal!
Great flavors here. Everything well balanced.

Reservations are a must because this space is small. I thoroughly enjoyed dining at mfk. last night. The service is prompt and provided a comfortable pace without feeling rushed or forgotten. Everything from the butter to the sardines to the scallops to the amazing tortilla espanola to the basque cake was delicious. The cocktails were tasty and unusual and Ben's wine recommendation was the perfect pairing. Can't wait to go back!
A truly exceptional meal!  Best restaurant in Lakeview by a landslide.  Highly recommend!
Great food, even better service. Lovely find during our visit to Chicago. Will be back next time!!
The Prawns are a must try! Very intimate setting. Make reservations prior.

I so wanted to love everything about our experience here, as this was a special birthday splurge for my husband. We had reservations and were seated right away, which was nice. The staff was attentive and friendly, so also no complaints there. Unfortunately it was incredibly hot in the restaurant and it was hard to focus on anything else. It wasn’t just us to notice it- the table next to us complained as well. If there was an issue with the ac we would have appreciated a heads up in advance and come back at a different time. If that’s how it always is, they should really look into getting that fixed. The dishes we ordered we fine, but the shellfish/pork/noodles at the end was way too heavy of a meal to enjoy in the heat, which was really unfortunate because it smelled delicious. We had plans to go out after dinner but we were too hot and sweaty afterwards and the whole thing just put a buzzkill on the night. For those price points we had expected a much more comfortable dining experience.

Unassuming location, big surprise.  I found mfk. on a list of Michelin honorable mentions.  I've walked past numerous times, so I was very surprised they'd get a nod from Michelin.  Get a reservation, it's small and busy.  I was surprised by the fresh and seaside decor, I didn't expect much at all before arriving.  The space is well adorned and pleasant.   Our server was very friendly and helpful in recommending favorites.  The Basque inspired small plates were all amazing.  We were delighted and surprised by each one.  We started with the mussels escabeche followed by an anchovy special.  After our smoked trout toast, there was a pause.   We didn't much notice, but our server came to apologize for the delay with another of the specials, fried avocado.  Everything had been so delicious, we certainly did not mind waiting for the next course.  The consideration of the kitchen was much appreciated.  The star of our evening was the tortilla espanola.  Having lived in Spain, I thought I knew what we were getting.  By the way, I love tortilla.  This was so different.  mfk. chefs reinvented tortilla.  It is so light, fluffy, and dreamy.  After two bites of the tortilla, I said, "wow, I could not make this at home."  Couldn't recommend mfk. enough!
Food wasnt really flavored, and customer service needs work.
Absolutely delicious.  Cordial service.  Curated beverage list compliments the food perfectly.

Cute little space with elegantly presented dishes. I ordered the meatballs and basque cake.  Meatballs were delicious and filling. The accompanying side complemented the dish  really well by providing a little citrus.  The basque cake was tasty but a little dry, didn't live up to the hype online.
Delicious,  interesting dishes.  Cozy atmosphere,  attentive service.
Delicous tapas. Must have the croquettes. The smoked chicken was also savory and tasty.
Food was delicious. Each dish was different and yet went together well.

Absolute gem in the neighbourhood and in Chicago on whole.  Amazingly prepared seafood and other Spanish inspired dishes.  Seafood Fideos, boquerones, tortilla espñola were some of the group favourites.  Can’t wait to go back to try more.
A hidden gem! Lovely staff and great food! We will definitely be back.

My friends and I had a craving for steamed seafood and this place didn't disappoint. I've been to a place similar to mfk. restaurant where they steam fresh seafood for you but the organization and process at mfk. restaurant was a bit different.
Delicious food. Friendly staff. Small quaint dining space. A little pricey but worth it.
Just go
Tiny, awesome. some of it is pretty adventurous, some of it is Spanish standard, but its clear it is being made by someone who cares.
Wonderful, fresh gourmet cuisine!
Great food. Great service.

Positively unique and delicious Spanish inspired fare. Add highly skilled bartenders and servers in a bright intimate setting. Porron pours all day and night. Albondingas and croquettes always on my plate. If you live in Chicago you gotta try MFK.
Everything we had was fresh, flavorful and delicious. Great service and friendly servers!

The perfect definition of a neighborhood gem.  Over the years, mfk. has consistently been my favorite restaurant in Chicago!  Plenty of reasons keep me coming back- super friendly and knowledgeable staff, curated coastal wine selections, rotating menu with new and exciting dishes, as well as my treasured staples: suzuki crudo, boquerones, cantabrian salt-cured anchovies and Basque cake!  Always so much fun, mfk. even taught me how to drink from a porron... Cheers!
I felt this place was very overpriced, REALLY expensive and was a bit of a hustle (ie being overly encouraged to spend more money!)
Superb Spanish cuisine, one of the best restaurants in the city!
Terriffic Spanish spot
Wow! Excellent!

Every dish was a delight for my tastebuds  and my eyes. Such beautiful presentation and such great flavors. My favorite dish that we had was Gambas al Ajillo and my least favorite was the Spanish tortilla with a creamy fish sauce, but everything was delicious. Their coffee on the hand needs to be better. They demanded a credit card to make sure we showed up for our reservation, but we were the only diners there the whole time.
Amazing and delicious
Excellent food and service.
Excellent seafood from anchovies to perfectly grilled octopus. The choice of wines are excellent!

A very cute and quaint space. The cocktails are tasty but a bit overpriced, as is the food. This place is certainly above average but again, too pricey for the quality. This makes me want to go to other restaurants that are even better and less or maybe equally pricey, but more worth it. Additionally, the service is OK. We watched our bartender and the (we think) hostess staring at their phones a good portion of our meal. Very unprofessional and unwelcoming. The busser however was very friendly and engaging. Unfortunately, we probably won't return.
Fabulous - one of the few places I would recommend sitting at the bar. Jason is an amazing bartender and server!

Food was good, atmosphere and service were good but portion sizes were extremely small for the cost. I came here for a late lunch recently and the bill was over 130$ for three people  and I left feeling like I needed more to eat. Bread here is extremely good but you also have to pay for it... This would be a  10/10 if the prices were more reasonable.
Fabulous food and great staff.

Pretentious little place. Mostly the food was excellent but I'm still feeling the effects of all the salt. The cod quiche dish is a pass but the other dishes were very flavorful and not at all skimpy considering it is a tapas place.
So delicious. Small menu with different options everyday. Shared plates - we had 4 and that was a pretty good amount between 2 people.

I can't remember what i ate entirely but the escargot was really good! It's a great shared plate restaurant. Very small, might want to book a reservation as it fills up very quickly after 5. I really enjoyed my time here and will go back. Very cozy and tons of greenery. It's easy to miss from the street as it's kind of a basement.

Really impressed. Was in the area for a short time. The chef is ambitious and creative. Exquisite flavors and service.  Ben was awesome at the bar. I felt like I was transported to a different place like Portland where it’s very personable and fresh. Thanks guys!
A great surprise! Albondigas, croquettes, cantabrican anchovis, spanish tostas, gazpacho and salmorejo were awesome!
Fantastic neighborhood place!!  Amazingly talented head chef, great service, great staff, and fabulous food!!
Loved the food here. It's a tiny place with a few tables along one wall and bar seating. It did get a little noisy at times but the food made up for that.
The food was excellent, the service OK, definitely worth the price and the food.
phenomenal experience! the food was just so good, i've never had anything like it! the atmosphere was so charming and comfortable. i would love to come back, words cannot do it justice.
Great seafood and service!
Was visiting my son from Toronto and we went here for Father’s Day dinner. It was fantastic. Every dish was beyond expectation. Very well seasoned food and well prepared. A real gem.
Love the food in this hidden gem of a place
Good but expensive of the experience
Spanish inspired sea food. Great service, good and cocktails
Loved this small restaurant. They dont have a fridge, so everything is prepared after you order. Fresh, unusual small dishes, some of them tastier than others. Unique experience
Excellent food, great atmosphere and service!

A shocking experience……  We were a party of four who came from France and England to see our cousins who live in Chicago. We wanted to have a quiet, convivial evening in a cozy restaurant with good food to enjoy our getting together again. The evening started off really enjoyably, we discussed the excellent one-woman play about racism “Until the Flood” which we had seen the night before. We talked about family, the state of the US economy, the imposition of trade tariffs and, of course, the news about what was going on related to the White House drama. Out of the blue the bar manager, who had been hovering, came to our table and announced aggressively that “talking about politics and religion is not permitted in this restaurant”. On questioning he repeated the statement. This unexpected intrusion into our private sphere spoilt what had so far been a pleasant evening. We cannot recommend this restaurant in which the management listens in on and censors the conversations of its patrons.

All details are considered here to be unique and original. I LOVE the wine list, the menu is short and super interesting. The fried prawn heads are incredibly fun and original. I thought I've seen it all in NY, but then these guys surprise you. The staff is just fantastic and engaging! You won't leave here disappointed! Can t wait to go back again. Oh, and it's super cozy too.

Excellent food! Very good place for Mexican food. The super deluxe is the best burrito ive ever had and no ones even close.. That alone is worth the trip. Even my fiance who isnt a burrito lover got one took a bite and said. Wow!!  Thanks guys!
From start to finish this restaurant was amazing. The food is incredible and the staff is wonderful!
Excellent food in a very cozy space. Service was impeccable as well!

Loved the food, service, and wine selection. Great atmosphere very quaint. Seems like a good place to go for a couple or small group. We had anchovies, crispy prawn heads, a hearty mushroom dish, and a pork/veal polenta sausage meatball dish;  they were all delicious. Spicing was excellent; reminded me somewhat of basque style cooking/pinxtos.
Small, great service, great food !

Eating at MFK made me feel like I was back where I grew up - on tip of the Texas Gulf coast at the nexus of Mexican flavors, warm weather, and seafood galore. My husband and I started with ceviche so tender it almost pulsed in my mouth, warm and bright and bursting with flavor. The rest of the meal was satisfying and right on but i won’t bore you with the details. This place feels special, with an intimacy born from its small basement-level space and a barmaid and bartender so low-key and friendly that they felt like inconspicuous old friends. Great service and great food!

Wonderful date night place that is especially cozy in the winter months. We sat at the bar, which was very comfortable and made sharing plates even easier. The bartender was our waiter and he was incredibly attentive. We will be back on a weekend night for the whole fish, but none of the dishes disappointed.
Every dish was amazing. Highly recommend mfk. Awesome cocktail menu too.

came here on a Tuesday and it was loud and packed. We managed to get a table, since we offered to share if others came in. Its a cute little space, feels very New York. The servers are very good and helpful and they have great drinks. I tried the Flight of the Opera and found it interesting and well mixed. We ordered the fried avocado, the speck fritters and the scallops with grits. Overall, the food was tasty, with an eye for detail and flavors. I didnt like the avocado as much but I did like the speck and the sauce/ dip it comes with and I would always get the scallops here. I will try more seafood if Im back. Prices are a little high but its good quality food. Just dont expect a quiet evening :)
Small and intimate place with great seafood.
Lovely place!

We take at least two trips a year to Chicago to celebrate with friends and family. The highlight is always the food. mfk was our surprise treat this year. The wine and service was excellent, but what was most impressive was the timing and presentation of the wonderful food. Drop by on a Saturday, but give yourself time to enjoy the afternoon and meal,
Super delicious. Everything we had was great. My only regret is that I waited so long to come here.
Really tasty! Everything we took.
Great seafood, good drinks.  Fried Smelt and Scallop Ceviche specials were great!
Amazing food and delightful service
Delicious small plates
So. Good. Can't miss when in the area.
Hard to stop eating the Broccoli sauteed in anchovy butter - and the cantabrian anchovies on toast were delicious
I love this place. Not your typical Spanish restaurant. Focus on Northern Coastal Spanish. Small but that adds to the experience. Great wait staff/service.
Great food. Great drinks
I've been here a half dozen times over the years since it opened.  From major event celebrating to casual lunch, it's been exquisite every time.  My favorite restaurant in Chicago.

Went for dinner. Tip number one look at the specials board, there seems to be a good selection there beyond what is in the menu. You will need to order 2-4 plates each ranging lowest $10. Two if you are alone and double that if you are in pairs. The food is good, just the price points are a little high for items I've had elsewhere that are better. Staff is also really helpful. Went in around 9PM on a Friday and there was no wait.

Excellent dining experience.  We sat at the bar and watch MaryAnn make us some really delicious cocktails.  Ordered 4 different appetizers....all of them were spot on good, the ceviche and croquettes were my favorite.  Shared an entree, the albondigas, which was delicious.  Definitely coming back to this place next time I visit Chicago.
Dishes are very small
one of the best spanish restaurants in town.

Hidden gem of a restaurant. Healthy, fresh, TASTY, unique (mostly seafood) dishes. Short menu where all dishes are intended to be shared and are perfectly executed. Would definitely recommend the mussels and my girlfriend would urge you to order the ceviche. Well done MFK, keep it up!
Amazing!! Everything was delicious

We discovered MFK in our neighborhood around a year ago and it has quickly climbed to the top ranks of our favorite restaurants in the Lakeview east neighborhood.  Both the food and drink menus are concise and delicious; certainly on-par or better than most restaurants in the area.  The menu is seasonal and includes fresh seafood-based dishes.  There are also adorable, season-appropriate drinks.  For example, last summer they served a drink for two in a copper pineapple.. and the drink was on fire (literally flaming).  Where this restaurant has everything else beat is ambiance.  MFK makes superb use of its intimate, garden-level space.  There are a handful of tables in the entire restaurant and less than 20 bar-seats, almost small enough to give the feeling that you are at a dinner party.  There is frequent banter between tables and it makes for a fun atmosphere.  Music selection is deliberate and unexpected the last weekend they played Beck's Midnight Vulture album in it's entirety.  The time before that Sky Ferreira's Night Time, My Time... in it's entirety.  Volume level of both ambient noise and music is kept in check, and unlike most restaurants, you can actually hear what people are saying.  Never been disappointed.

Called and was told. "You don't need a reservation before 7pm. Drove in and arrived at 4pm to be received with the question "Do you have a reservation?" SMH  So, tip of the day. Regardless of what they say. Make a reservation, or go elsewhere.
mfk is small, quiet, cool, great service and the food is fresh, flavorful and delicious.  Our new favorite spot.  Drinks are great too.  Sitting at the bar for dinner is a fun casual way to go.
Great drinks and food. Always fun to go here. Staff are very personable and helpful.
Cute place...sat next to kitchen.  Great service and food hit the mark.

My favorite Chicago restaurant by far. Very intimate and it's all about the food and drink. The food is very seafood focused but they always have a few good meat options. Drinks alone are worth coming for as well. You can tell there is real passion here.

Small restaurant but everything is delicious. There's usually seating at the bar for those walking in. Otherwise reservations are held with a credit card. The bread service is nice for groups since you can have unlimited bread. It does take a little time from when you ask since they toast the bread for you. Highly recommend the saffron toasted vermicelli noodles, squid ink tostada ceviche, as wells as the saffron rice seafood bowl. The menu does change on occasion.
Really good small plates and seafood at this cozy restaurant
Intimate, friendly, impeccably prepared Spanish tinged seafood.
Amazing food . helpful staff
Tiny place serving absolutely fabulous food. But be warned, it's close quarters.
Great service!!! Food was great but just shy of 5 *
Delicious food from start to finish with several interesting wines by the glass. Really fun place to share small plates and enjoy fresh and tasty Spanish inspired seafood.

Sensational. Prawns with sobrasada, chilled cauliflower, seafood fideuà, green papaya salad & some txacolina to pair. Set up is small, intimate, service is efficient, helpful. Go, sit at the bar, and graze.
Awesome place for tapas and mariscos in a relatively relaxed environment - their cocktails are also excellent.  Definitely don't miss out on the mussels or scallops both amazing.
Just, WOW!  This is definitely a Chicago must.  Top notch sea food tapas.  I can't say enough great things about this place.  Staff is incredibly friendly as well.
Fabulous food, atmosphere and drinks. Casual yet upscale in quality. Need to come by for a bite if you are ever in the city.

If you appreciate excellent, fresh (nothing frozen!), skillfully and beautifully prepared food, especially seafood, you must eat here. Thoughtfully crafted cocktails and wine selection complement the cuisine, as does the knowledgeable and friendly staff.  Two things of note if you've never been here:  1) Certain dishes do take longer than others (roasting a half-chicken is NOT a quick process, folks) so order accordingly, then order a drink and relax. It's all worth the wait.  2) Make a reservation, especially if you are coming in a group larger than two, as the space is very small — they are often solidly booked (yes, even on Mondays) — and the bar, which is quite comfortable and runs adjacent to the table area, is likely the only way you're going to get a seat if you DIDN'T make a reservation.  The menu has just enough options, in my opinion — there are some vegetarian choices and also a few meat dishes for you hardcore carnivores, but everything else features fish/seafood (the ceviche and boquerones are both exquisite). Most of the menu items are smaller plates, so you can try things you might not otherwise. I've never been disappointed here, only impressed.
The prawns were seasoned shells, the goofy pallea I wouldn't feed to my dog, it takes them 40 minutes to make chicken, and they pout you at the bar because of it, while the tables are kept empty.
Stand-out food with exceptional service. Snails, ceviche, and crispy prawn heads were delicious. Highly recommend.
We went for brunch.  Had fab food!! Great glass of rose.

Food to remember. Each of the four dishes we shared were heavenly. Still thinking about them and the wonderful experience. Great passion in the air. I hope to get back to Chicago before the after taste wanes.

Tried this on a summer night after a museum day. My favorite part was the seersucker pocketsquaresque napkins, and the cocktails.  We were seated right away at the bar with no reservation. It was too crowded and too loud for a Chicago dinner. (Srsly... half of Dan the wine supplier's ass was on my barstool, but he and Kate made good on it by giving some awesome food recs in town).  Around 8pm a huuuge party rolled in and the volume just escalated to beyond unpleasant... since everyone now had to yell to be heard.  Food was okay. The standouts were the tempura avocado, and the 1/2 lb skewered shrimp. We also tried ceviche, fregola, boquerones... which were all so-so. Service was confused and disorganized,  but im sure as its a new place theyll get it together soon.  I would try this place again if im in the area and if they take out a few place settings so that im not eating off my neighbor's plate or hearing about how hairy Jeff's back was. Fantabulous craft beer bar across the street!
Honestly, there's not a single bad item on the menu. I highly recommend all of the anchovies, along with the octopus or any drink on the menu.
Fantastic food and wonderful people. They love the food that they serve, and it shows.
Awesome. Each dish was  a treat
Sari & Scott....  Wish we could eat at MFK every day!  After our amazing dinner on July 4th, we can't wait to work our way through the rest of your menu!  Congrats.
